The [[Standard year/Legends|year]] '''17,000 before the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]] ([[Galactic Standard Calendar|BBY]])''' was a span of [[Time/Legends|time]] in the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic's]] [[Indecta Era]] that occurred during the [[First Alsakan Conflict]]. During the conflict, which had begun [[17,018 BBY|eighteen years]] previously, [[Arkanian/Legends|Arkanian]] [[Geneticist/Legends|scientists]], who were seeking to perform genetic experiment on [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Species/Legends|species]], discovered the primitive [[Xexto/Legends|Xexto]] on [[Troiken/Legends|Troiken]]. The Arkanians took a sample of the species and moved them to nearby [[Quermia/Legends|Quermia]], where both groups were experimented upon.

==Proem==
{{Quote|The Republic's Great Manifest period (20,000&ndash;17,000 BBY) marked an increased movement into the Rimward territories of the Slice, which became known as the Expansion Region.|From the text of ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' by [[Voren Na'al/Legends|Voren Na'al]]|<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref>}}
The [[Great Manifest Period/Legends|Great Manifest Period]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] was a [[Time/Legends|time]] of expansion within the then-known [[galactic community]]. [[Planet/Legends|Planetary]] governments and corporate interests were rapidly expanding into [[The Slice/Legends|the Slice]] in order to claim new worlds for settlement and exploitation of natural resources. In the northern portion of this region, near the [[Perlemian Trade Route/Legends|Perlemian Trade Route]], the planets of [[Alsakan/Legends|Alsakan]] and [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] were fervently competing against each other,<ref name="EA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> with hostilities brewing as the two planets fought for dominance economically and culturally.<ref name="EA" /><ref name="WW">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/source/writtenword/index.html?page=1|text=The Written Word|int=The Written Word}}</ref> Furthermore, the Republic's bureaucracy and [[Politics/Legends|politicking]] grew with fervor, fueling the rivalry as [[Sector/Legends|sectors]] of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] had become [[Rule of Fifty|so large]] that they were ungovernable. The growing governmental structure included the creation of the [[Bureau of Ships and Services/Legends|Bureau of Ships and Services]] more than one thousand [[Standard year/Legends|years]] prior to the conclusion of the Great Manifest Period. This organization was created to help regulate [[Star/Legends|interstellar]] trade as well as to maintain records of [[Starship/Legends|starship]] transactions and movements.<ref name="EA" /> Furthermore, the intensifying strife between Alsakan and Coruscant had reached a boiling point. Initially, the conflict started as a [[Blockade/Legends|blockade]]. Soon thereafter, however, the event escalated into actual fighting. An outright civil war was only avoided by legislation passed by the Bureau of Ships and Services. With legislation in place, the specific conflict settled. Nevertheless, economic advantages in the Expansion Region were not the only motivating factors for open war.<ref name="EA" /> Alsakan also desired to usurp the [[Capital/Legends|seat of government]] from Coruscant,<ref name="NEC" /> believing it to be their deserved place in the galaxy.<ref name="WW" /> As a result, the motivations behind the fighting went unresolved.<ref name="EA" /> Open warfare began in [[17,018 BBY]] with the Republic [[Republic assault on Virujansi|assault and capture]] of [[Virujansi/Legends|Virujansi]].<ref name="EGW" />

==The galaxy in 17,000 BBY==
While the Republic was busied with the [[First Alsakan Conflict]], the arboreal hunter-gatherer [[Xexto/Legends|Xexto]] [[Species/Legends|species]] of [[Troiken/Legends|Troiken]] was discovered by rogue [[Geneticist/Legends|scientists]] from [[Arkania/Legends|Arkania]].<ref name="NEC" /><ref name="CSWE">''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''</ref> The [[Scientist/Legends|scientists]] sought to perform genetic experimentation on [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] species outside of the Republic's borders,<ref name="UAA">''[[Ultimate Alien Anthology]]''</ref> because such actions were illegal within Republic [[Realspace/Legends|space]].<ref name="NEC" /> Around 17,000 BBY, the [[Arkanian/Legends|Arkanian]] scientists secretly took a sample of the Xexto and relocated them to the nearby planet [[Quermia/Legends|Quermia]]. There, the planet was [[Terraforming/Legends|terraformed]], and the transplanted Xexto became helpless subjects of genetic experimentation and manipulation. The experiments were not confined to Quermia, however, as the Arkanians also performed some experiments on those who had remained behind on Troiken.<ref name="UAA" />

==Impact==
{{Quote|While the fighting never expanded to a full-scale civil war in the Republic, the first of the Alsakan Conflicts ended the boom of the Great Manifest Period. However, it did not end Alsakan's ambitions, and the Alsakanese would continue to attempt to claim their "rightful" place as galactic capital for another 14,000 years.|[[Doctor/Legends|Dr.]] [[Milanda Vorgan]]|<ref name="WW" />}}
Inside the Republic, the conflict between Alsakan and Coruscant was the first of [[Alsakan Conflicts/Legends|seventeen such skirmishes]] between the two planets.<ref name="EA" /> While the Bureau of Ships and Services was able to intervene in the first Alsakan Conflict,<ref name="EGW" /> the desire to usurp the capital coupled with the competition in the Slice caused periodic unrest until the [[Seventeenth Alsakan Conflict|final conflict]] occurred in [[3017 BBY]]. The seventeen conflicts destroyed historical landmarks, such as [[Belgoth's Beacon]] and the [[Alsakan Mosaics]], and laid waste to portions of the Expansion Region.<ref name="EA" />

The group of Xexto that underwent genetic experimentation on Quermia by Arkanian scientists were monitored and tested for only a few generations.<ref name="CSWE" /> At that point, the geneticists abandoned their research, fearing the wrath of the Republic. They instead turned their focus to other projects. Nevertheless, permanent alterations to the Xexto on Troiken had taken hold. On Quermia, the dramatically altered subjects were left to develop within the natural processes, and they became the [[Quermian/Legends|Quermian]] species. Both the Xexto and Quermians became technologically-developed societies independent of each other. After both species were discovered by the broader [[galactic community]], it became a commonly held belief that they were genetically related.<ref name="UAA" /> The connection between Quermians and Xexto was discovered millennia after their forced genetic divergence, but the Xexto initially refused to acknowledge it.<ref name="CSWE" /> Eventually, however, they reluctantly accepted what genetic tests had verified.<ref name="UAA" />

==Notable events==
*The Xexto species<ref name="NEC" /> was discovered by Arkanian scientists and the process of genetic experimentation began on the primitive species. {{Circa}}<ref name="UAA" />

==Behind the scenes==
The year 17,000 BBY is first mentioned in ''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]'',<ref name="Characters">''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]''</ref> a reference book published on [[April 23]], [[2002]],<ref name="Characters-Date">{{SWArchive|url=eu/lit/novel/news20020212.html|text=Book Preview: The New Essential Guide}}</ref> and has received mentions in various reference material in the years that followed.<ref name="UAA" /><ref name="CSWE" /> ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' in [[2005]] established the starting date for the Alsakan Conflicts as 17,000 BBY,<ref name="NEC" /> though ''[[The Essential Guide to Warfare]]'' later moved that to [[17,018 BBY]].<ref name="EGW" />

